On Thursday, the Federal District Court of Appeal suspended enforcement of a court order demanding changes to the "Stop and Frisk" program of the New York Police Department, and the judge dismissed the case.
The United States Second Circuit Court of Appeals judge Sheindlin Shiry said that execution of decisions will be suspended pending the results of an appeal filed against the city.
In August, a judge ruled that the city violated the constitution in how it carried out the program for street detention and questioning.
