"I spend a lot of time calming parents — usually it does not mean the rapid advance of full sexual maturity," said Kaplovitts.
Obvious signs of development, such as growing breasts and pubic hair appear earlier in girls.
But there is only a slight shift in the age of menustration (first period) over the last four decades.
In the United States, the average age is 12.5 years and decreased compared with 12.75 years in 1970.
"After breasts begin to develop, is at least two to three years before menustration", — said Kaplovitts, who is also the author of "Early Puberty In Girls: How To Cope With This Widespread Problem."
Time is the most accurate check of how puberty will advance.
There is debate about what constitutes an active sexual maturity, but is considered "premature" when breast increase is accompanied by a sharp rise in growth to 8 years.
In most cases, the process will slow and the pediatrician can monitor carefully.
More rapid progress can serve as the basis for endocrologist analysis to avoid serious problems, such as a tumor or cyst.
There are procedures to delay early menstruation and prevent another consequence: premature aging of bones, which ultimately can lead to slow growth and low growth in adulthood.
Recommendations for drug or hormone therapy is based on the age of the child, the level of development, growth rates and emotional maturity.
